resources.string:
What is SQL? 
 • SQL stands for Structured Query Language 
 • Used for storing, manipulating and retrieving data within relational databases 


Commands: 
 • SELECT: Used to select data from a database, which is then returned in a results set. Example is SELECT * FROM users; 
 • TRUNCATE TABLE: Similar to DROP, but instead of deleting the table and its data, this deletes only the data. Example is TRUNCATE TABLE sessions; 
 • UNION: Combines the results from 2 or more SELECT statements and returns only distinct values. Example is SELECT city FROM events UNION SELECT city from subscribers; 
 • UPDATE: Updates existing data in a table. Example is UPDATE cars SET mileage = 23500, serviceDue = 0 WHERE id = 45;
